petition board~
The @@ypetition board@@N is a tall oak frame bolted to an iron post, its surface divided into columns by copper tacks.  Notices in varying states of decay record complaints about road conditions, toll disputes, and claims for lost cargo, each stamped with the dated seal of the @@BMagistrate Ledgerhouse@@N.  The oldest readable entry demands reimbursement for a broken axle caused by a drainage gap that has since been repaired.
~
E
charter marker slabs~
The @@Wcharter marker slabs@@N are rectangular stone uprights spaced at regular intervals along the road's edge.  Each bears inscriptions in three eras of script, the oldest barely legible and the newest in crisp Midgaard charter-hand.  The most common text is a jurisdictional declaration: @@W"By order of the Magistrate Ledgerhouse, this road stands under continuous charter authority."@@N  Beneath the newest text, traces of older declarations in unfamiliar script are still faintly visible.
~
