The @@pancient stone bridge@@N is a single-arch span of dressed stone, its blocks fitted with a precision that surpasses anything built in the modern era.  The keystones are carved with interlocking geometric patterns, and the mortar joints are so fine they are almost invisible.  Despite the ages, not a single stone has shifted.
